a memory comprising a first memory section storing computer-executable instructions and a second memory section storing:
an enrolled document template including at least one enrolled document color profile descriptor;
region of interest (ROI) information; and
a codebook representing partitions of a color space;

receive a first image of the subject identification document, the first image depicting, in a red-green-blue (RGB) color space, the subject identification document;
transform the first image of the subject document to a second image of the subject identification document in a YcbCr color space;
assign pixels within a ROI in the second image corresponding to the ROI information to the partitions of the codebook;
generate a subject document color profile descriptor based on respective counts of the pixels assigned to the partitions of the codebook;
compare the subject document color profile descriptor to the enrolled document color profile descriptor to determine whether the subject identification document is authentic.

representing the pixels within the ROI as a plurality of (cb, cr) points in a [Cb, Cr] color plane;
computing respective distances between each of the plurality of (cb, cr) points and each of respective centroids in the [Cb, Cr] color plane corresponding to the partitions of the codebook; and
assigning each of the plurality of (cb, cr) points to a nearest partition based on the respective distances.

representing a first histogram for the enrolled document color profile descriptor as a first vector;
representing a second histogram for the subject document color profile descriptor as a second vector having elements corresponding to the respective counts of the pixels assigned to the partitions of the codebook; and
computing a cosine distance between the first vector and the second vector, the cosine distance being the matching score.

receiving a first image of a corresponding enrollment document, the first image depicting, in the RGB color space, the enrollment document;
transforming the first image of the enrollment document to a second image of the enrollment document in the YcbCr color space;
assigning pixels within the ROI in the second image of the enrollment document corresponding to the ROI information to the partitions of the codebook; and
generating the enrolled document color profile descriptor based on respective counts of the pixels within the ROI of the enrollment document assigned to the partitions of the codebook.

receive a first image of a subject identification document, the first image depicting, in a red-green-blue (RGB) color space, the subject identification document;
transform the first image of the subject document to a second image of the subject identification document in a YCbCr color space;
assign pixels within a ROI in the second image corresponding to the ROI information to partitions of the [Cb, Cr] color plane defined in the codebook;
generate a subject document color profile descriptor based on respective counts of the pixels assigned to the partitions of the codebook;
compare the subject document color profile descriptor to the enrolled document color profile descriptor to determine whether the subject identification document is authentic.

